---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | RealityFoundation" active="about">
  <div class="pb-8 border-b mb-10" style="border-color: var(--color-line);">
    <p class="mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--color-muted);">About</p>
    <h1>RealityFoundation</h1>
    <p>
      An independent European research foundation dedicated to the study of
      digital authenticity, synthetic media, and the academic frameworks needed
      to preserve verifiable reality.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid gap-12 items-start" style="grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr; padding-top: 1rem;">
    <nav class="aside-sticky aside-nav" aria-label="Page sections">
      <a href="#mission" class="nav-link active">Mission</a>
      <a href="#values" class="nav-link">Values</a>
      <a href="#structure" class="nav-link">Structure</a>
      <a href="#team" class="nav-link">Team</a>
      <!-- <a href="#realitycheck" class="nav-link">RealityCheck</a> -->
    </nav>

    <div>
      <section id="mission" class="mb-16">
        <h2
          style="font-size:var(--text-lg); letter-spacing:0.04em; text-transform:uppercase; margin-bottom:var(--space-6);"
        >
          Mission
        </h2>
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <p>
            RealityFoundation exists to produce independent, peer-reviewed
            research at the intersection of digital media, cryptography, and
            legal evidence. We believe that the integrity of visual records is a
            public good — and that it is currently undefended.
          </p>
          <p>
            Generative AI has broken the naive assumption that images are
            evidence. Deepfakes have moved from novelty to threat. Insurance
            fraud, judicial proceedings, news verification, and historical
            archives are all affected. <strong
              >No independent academic institution has made this its primary
              focus.</strong
            > We do.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our research informs tooling, policy, and standards. Our
            publications are open access. Our methods are open source wherever
            possible. We collaborate with universities, regulators, and civil
            society organisations across Europe and beyond.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-none border-t my-8" style="border-color: var(--color-line);" />

      <section id="values" class="mb-16">
        <h2
          style="font-size:var(--text-lg); letter-spacing:0.04em; text-transform:uppercase; margin-bottom:var(--space-6);"
        >
          Values
        </h2>
        <div class="grid gap-4" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(min(380px, 100%), 1fr));">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Independence</h3>
            <p>
              We do not accept funding from organisations with a commercial
              interest in our findings. Our conclusions are our own.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Openness</h3>
            <p>
              Research outputs are published open access. Datasets and
              methodologies are shared with the scientific community.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Rigour</h3>
            <p>
              We hold ourselves to the standards of peer review,
              reproducibility, and transparent methodology in all published
              work.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Impact</h3>
            <p>
              Academic work must reach decision-makers. We actively translate
              research into policy briefs, public explainers, and practical
              tools.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-none border-t my-8" style="border-color: var(--color-line);" />

      <section id="structure" class="mb-16">
        <h2
          style="font-size:var(--text-lg); letter-spacing:0.04em; text-transform:uppercase; margin-bottom:var(--space-6);"
        >
          Structure
        </h2>
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <p>
            RealityFoundation is incorporated as an independent non-profit
            foundation under European law. It is governed by a <strong
              >Scientific Committee</strong
            > responsible for research direction and publication standards, and a
            <strong>Board of Directors</strong> responsible for governance and strategic
            decisions.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Scientific Committee includes external academic advisors from
            computer science, law, and media studies. Membership criteria,
            conflict-of-interest policies, and committee minutes will be
            published on this site as the governance structure matures.
          </p>
          <h2>Scientific Committee</h2>
          <p>
            The Scientific Committee is being formed. If you are a researcher
            whose work intersects with digital authenticity, synthetic media
            detection, cryptographic provenance, or media law and you are
            interested in joining, please <a href="/get-involved"
              >get in touch</a
            >.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-none border-t my-8" style="border-color: var(--color-line);" />

      <section id="team" class="mb-16">
        <h2
          style="font-size:var(--text-lg); letter-spacing:0.04em; text-transform:uppercase; margin-bottom:var(--space-6);"
        >
          Founding Team
        </h2>
        <div class="grid gap-4" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(min(380px, 100%), 1fr));">
          <div class="card">
            <p class="card-eyebrow">Co-founder</p>
            <h3>Emilio Dalla Torre</h3>
            <p style="font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--mono-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.04em;">Technology Lead</p>
            <p>
              Emilio holds a background in Engineering Physics and is completing a Double Degree Master in HPC Engineering and ICT Innovation at Politecnico di Milano and KTH Royal Institute of Technology. He has worked across full-stack engineering, AI systems, and large-scale infrastructure at PwC, Accenture, and Qualcomm. He leads RealityFoundation's technical research agenda and systems architecture.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <p class="card-eyebrow">Co-founder</p>
            <h3>Bianca Illing</h3>
            <p style="font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--mono-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.04em;">Research Lead</p>
            <p>
              Bianca holds an MSc in Economics from Nova SBE and a BSc in Business Administration from ESCP. She has worked in strategy consulting and is currently Founder's Associate at greenmetrics.ai, where she focuses on AI applications for climate resilience. She leads RealityFoundation's research programme and academic partnerships.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <p class="card-eyebrow">Co-founder</p>
            <h3>Gaia Dalla Zonca</h3>
            <p style="font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--mono-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.04em;">Operations Lead</p>
            <p>
              Gaia holds a CEMS Master in International Management from Nova SBE and FGV-EAESP, and a Bachelor in International Politics and Government from Bocconi University. She currently works at EY. She leads RealityFoundation's operations, governance, and institutional relationships.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!--
      <hr class="border-none border-t my-8" style="border-color: var(--color-line);" />

      <section id="realitycheck" class="mb-16">
        <h2
          style="font-size:var(--text-lg); letter-spacing:0.04em; text-transform:uppercase; margin-bottom:var(--space-6);"
        >
          Relationship with RealityCheck
        </h2>
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <p>
            RealityCheck is a consumer and professional application that allows
            users to capture images and store cryptographic proofs on the
            blockchain, establishing authenticity at the moment of capture.
            RealityFoundation is its independent academic counterpart.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong
              >The Foundation does not develop or commercialise the RealityCheck
              product.</strong
            > Its role is to provide independent scientific validation of the methods
            used, publish the underlying research, and ensure that the standards employed
            are defensible in legal and academic contexts.
          </p>
          <p>
            This separation is intentional. Users, regulators, and courts should
            be able to rely on Foundation research precisely because it is not
            produced by the company that benefits commercially from its
            findings.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
      -->
      
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.nav-link');
    const sections = document.querySelectorAll('section[id]');

    const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
      entries.forEach((entry) => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          navLinks.forEach((link) => link.classList.remove('active'));
          const activeLink = document.querySelector(
            `.nav-link[href="#${entry.target.id}"]`
          );
          if (activeLink) {
            activeLink.classList.add('active');
          }
        }
      });
    }, { threshold: 0.3 });

    sections.forEach((section) => observer.observe(section));
  </script>
</BaseLayout>
